short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: This extension corrects all misspellings of 'woah' to 'whoa'

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
Woah --> Whoa

Does a little bit of your soul break off every time someone writes "woah" on the internet and your brain initially rhymes it with "noah?" Does it seem to grow worse with each passing year as proliferating misspellings of this word accumulate uncorrected on countless webpages? Then install this extension, keep your soul intact, and never encounter this dumb problem again.
